article.headline: Seattle Pacific 76, Murray State 68
article.story: MORAGA, Calif. (AP) -- Seattle Pacific's Dustin Bremerman hit three 3-pointers in the first five minutes of play as the Division II Falcons defeated Murray State 76-68 in the Shamrock Invitational at Saint Mary's College on Saturday. Seattle Pacific (1-1) never trailed in its victory over the defending Ohio Valley Conference champions, shooting 10-for-21 from 3-point range. Murray State, which lost on a buzzer-beating 3-pointer from halfcourt to San Diego State on Friday, is 0-2. Bremerman led all scorers with 21 points, forming a strong outside-inside attack with Rob Will, who had 19 points. Murray State, which returns with only one starter from its NCAA Tournament team that went 24-7 last year, out-shot Seattle Pacific from the floor, hitting 27 of 60 shots. But the Racers were only 2-of-12 from 3-point range, while the Falcons hit 11-of-32. Murray State never got closer than seven points despite holding Seattle Pacific scoreless from the floor for the final 7:24. Seattle Pacific hit 13 of 14 free throws during that period to remain safely in front. Seattle Pacific plays San Diego State while Murray State meets host Saint Mary's in the tournament's final games Sunday.
